IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDescription: PROMOTE AND PROVIDE MENTAL HEALTH SERVICES FOR THE WASHINGTON STATE DIVISION OF MENTAL HEALTH SERVICE AREA NO. 20, ENCOMPASSING KITTITAS, YAKIMA AND KLICKITAT COUNTIES.THE ORGANIZATION IS A STATE-LICENSED COMMUNITY MENTAL HEALTH CENTER THAT PROVIDES SERVICES FOR A SPECTRUM OF PROBLEMS RANGING FORM ACUTE, LIFE-THREATENING EMERGENCIES, TO LONG-STANDING PSYCHIATRIC ILLNESSES. IT ALSO PROVIDES CONSULTATION, TRAINING, AND EMPLOYEE ASSISTANCE SERIVCES. ITS CLIENTS INCLUDE CHILDREN, ADOLESCENTS, AUDULTS, SENIOR CITIZENS, AND BUSINESSES.

IRS990.Description: OUTPATIENT MENTAL HEALTH AND CHEMICAL DEPENDENCY SERVICES FOR CHILDREN, ADOLESCENTS AND ADULTS. APPROXIMATELY 11,648 INDIVIDUALS WERE SERVED DURING THE YEAR.

Activity2.Description: RESIDENTIAL MENTAL HEALTH PROGRAMS FOR CHRONICALLY MENTALLY ILL CLIENTS (CHILDREN, ADOLESCENTS AND ADULTS). A RANGE OF RESIDENTIAL PROGRAMS ARE OFFERED INCLUDING SUPPORTED LIVING APARTMENTS, GROUP AND BOARDING HOMES, INTENSIVE RESIDENTIAL TREATMENT FACILITIES AND INPATIENT PROGRAMS. APPROXIMATELY 1,116 INDIVIDUALS WERE SERVED DURING THE YEAR.

Activity3.Description: BEHAVIORAL HEALTH ACUTE CARE SERVICES FOR CLIENTS IN CRISIS. SERVICES INCLUDE A CRISIS TELEPHONE LINE, COMMUNITY CRISIS OUTREACH, EVALUATION AND CRISIS INTERVENTION, INVOLUNTARY TREATMENT EVALUATION AND PLACEMENT, JAIL DIVERSION AND OTHER ALTERNATIVES TO HOSPITALIZATION OR INSTITUTIONALIZATION. INCLUDES SERVICES TO VICTIMS OF CRIME INCLUDING SEXUAL ASSAULT, DOMESTIC VIOLENCE AND OTHER CRIMES. SERVICES INCLUDE VICTIM ADVOCACY, SUPPORT AND COUNSELING. APPROXIMATELY 2,824 INDIVIDUALS WERE SEVED DURING THE YEAR.
